<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Homollea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Homollea septentrionalis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homollea septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
De Block by the size and shape of the leaves of the first order bracts (broadly ovate to orbiculate, 5.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.2-9.5 cm vs. broadly ovate to ovate, 0.8-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-2.5 cm in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. septentrionalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the calyx tube and lobes which are glabrous inside (vs. densely sericeous), the lower number of ovules (3-4 vs. 4-6) and the different seeds (2 seeds with irregularly distributed surface ridges, ca. 8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.5 mm vs. 2-6 seeds with smooth surface, ca. 4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 mm).
</paragraph>
